Document and Resource Loading:
----------------------------
JavaScript can detect when HTML and resources are loaded.

DOMContentLoaded -	HTML fully loaded and parsed
load -	All resources (images, styles) loaded
beforeunload -	User leaving the page
unload -	Page unloading completely

Scripts: async and defer:
------------------------
<script> tags can load in parallel using async or defer.
async - As soon as loaded
defer - After DOM ready

Resource Loading: onload and onerror:
------------------------------------
Detect success or failure of loading resources.

let img = document.createElement("img");
img.src = "pic.jpg";

img.onload = () => alert("Image loaded");
img.onerror = () => alert("Image failed");

Mutation Observer:
-------------------
Allows watching for DOM changes.

Used for:
Detecting added/removed elements
Reacting to dynamic DOM changes

Selection and Range:
--------------------
Represents user-selected text or custom text ranges.

let sel = window.getSelection();
console.log(sel.toString());

Used for:
Custom text highlighting
Rich text editors
